# Stripe v17

ADR-005. `apiVersion` is pinned. Webhooks are atomically idempotent.

## API version

```ts
// src/lib/stripe/config.ts — DO NOT change apiVersion casually
import Stripe from "stripe";

export const stripe = new Stripe(process.env.STRIPE_SECRET_KEY!, {
  apiVersion: "2024-12-18.acacia",
  typescript: true,
});
```

Bumping the version requires a new ADR (or at minimum an entry in `/docs/BILLING-FLOWS.md` describing what changed).

## Reading subscription period

`current_period_end` is on `items.data[*]`, NOT on the subscription root, in `2024-12-*` and later:

```ts
import { getSubscriptionPeriod } from "@/lib/stripe/period";

const { currentPeriodStart, currentPeriodEnd } = getSubscriptionPeriod(sub);
// throws if the items array is empty — defensive, see Patch-02.
```

If you see `sub.current_period_end` in any new code, reject it.

## Webhook handler shape

Required pattern (Patch-03):

```ts
// 1. Verify signature
const event = stripe.webhooks.constructEvent(raw, sig, secret);

// 2. Atomic claim — race-safe idempotency
const claimed = await db.insert(stripeEvents).values({...})
  .onConflictDoNothing({ target: stripeEvents.eventId })
  .returning({ id: stripeEvents.id });

if (claimed.length === 0) {
  return NextResponse.json({ duplicate: true }); // 200
}

// 3. Dispatch
try {
  await handleStripeEvent(event);
  await db.update(stripeEvents).set({ succeeded: true, processedAt: new Date() })
    .where(eq(stripeEvents.id, claimed[0].id));
  return NextResponse.json({ ok: true });
} catch (err) {
  await db.update(stripeEvents).set({ error: String(err) })
    .where(eq(stripeEvents.id, claimed[0].id));
  return new Response("handler failed", { status: 500 });
}
```

Do NOT replace `onConflictDoNothing(...).returning(...)` with a SELECT-then-INSERT or a try/catch around INSERT. Both lose the race.

## Metadata

When creating Checkout sessions / customers, metadata gets:

```ts
metadata: {
  kclub_user_id: user.id, // our UUID, not Clerk's
  kclub_membership_type: "VIP", // enum value
}
```

NEVER put PII (email, name) in metadata. Stripe metadata is searchable in the Stripe Dashboard and shows up in support tickets.

## Membership transitions

Driven by webhook → call `applyMembershipTransition()`. Enforces the state machine in ADR-007. Never `UPDATE memberships.status` directly from a server action — go through the webhook (manual transitions are done by writing a synthetic event, which is rare and audit-logged).

## Customer Portal

Default account-management surface. Don't reimplement subscription cancel UI:

```ts
const session = await stripe.billingPortal.sessions.create({
  customer: user.stripeCustomerId,
  return_url: `${env.NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL}/m/billing`,
  configuration: env.STRIPE_PORTAL_CONFIGURATION_ID,
});

return Response.redirect(session.url, 303);
```

